    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-02-17T16:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-02-17T16:00:00-05:00" n="744"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d744">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">834.00 Revolutions/7: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in Paraguay</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Howard</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Asunción</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1936-02-17T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >February 17, 1936—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received 7:50 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>16. My 15, February 17, 9 a.m. Fighting in center of town continues with
                    undetermined results. General Estigarribia and Minister for Foreign Affairs
                    Riart are reliably reported to be prisoners of the insurgents. President Ayala
                    appears to be directing resistance either from one of the gunboats or the police
                    headquarters which together with marine barracks and the arsenals are said to
                    have remained loyal.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Howard</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
